Description: Body sherd of East Greek, possibly North Ionian, pottery closed vessel, possibly an amphora; exterior: possible cream slip (only traces remaining) and undetermined painted decoration; inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: M. Pesenti suggests this may be Attic. The clay seems too light, but is nowhere clearly visible.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 331)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 671, no. 292)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.018)
